  <h2>Why installation quality matters more than brand</h2>
  <p>Industry data is consistent: <strong>70% of new HVAC systems in the U.S. are installed incorrectly</strong> — wrong size, wrong refrigerant charge, or leaky ductwork. The result is a homeowner paying for a high-SEER2 system but running at closer to mid-teens efficiency, with shorter equipment life and bigger repair bills. The brand on the outside is the smallest part of the equation.</p>

  <p>Every I Care Air Care installation starts with a <strong>Manual-J heat load calculation</strong> — room by room, accounting for Florida sun orientation, window area, ceiling height, insulation level, and infiltration rate. We don't sell you a 4-ton because "that's what you had before." Many Wesley Chapel, New Tampa and Land O' Lakes homes were originally oversized, and rightsizing the new system alone improves humidity control dramatically.</p>

  <h2>Our installation process — 10 days from quote to comfort</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-700 mt-4">
    <li><strong>In-home consultation and Manual-J load calculation</strong> (about 90 minutes, no obligation)</li>
    <li><strong>Written proposal</strong> with 3 equipment tiers (good/better/best) — SEER2, warranty, monthly finance option all in one view</li>
    <li><strong>Permitting</strong> with the correct county (Pasco, Hillsborough or Polk)</li>
    <li><strong>Removal and disposal</strong> of your old system — refrigerant recovered per EPA rules</li>
    <li><strong>Ductwork inspection</strong> and any necessary re-sealing (often the cheapest efficiency gain)</li>
    <li><strong>New equipment installation</strong>: pad or rooftop mount, new line set or flush of existing, fresh disconnect, surge protector</li>
    <li><strong>Refrigerant evacuation</strong> to 500 microns and precise charge to manufacturer subcool spec</li>
    <li><strong>Electrical and thermostat commissioning</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Start-up, static pressure verification, temperature split test</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Homeowner walk-through</strong>, warranty registration, county inspection scheduled</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>What's changing in 2026: lower-GWP refrigerants</h2>
  <p>Newer residential AC and heat pump systems are moving away from R-410A and toward lower-GWP refrigerants such as R-454B and R-32. Two things for homeowners to know:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Some newer systems use mildly flammable A2L refrigerants and require updated tools, leak detection, manufacturer procedures, and jobsite safety steps.</li>
    <li>R-410A isn't illegal to repair or recharge — but it is increasingly expensive. If your R-410A system needs a major repair past 12 years old, the replacement math almost always wins.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Equipment we install in Tampa</h2>
  <p>We install and service the major brands Florida homeowners recognize, including <strong>Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Rheem, Goodman, American Standard, Bryant, and Mitsubishi Electric</strong> ductless mini-splits. Every proposal explains the included manufacturer warranty, optional maintenance coverage, and the workmanship warranty in writing before you approve the job.</p>

  <h2>Ductless mini-splits for additions and problem rooms</h2>
  <p>Adding a room above the garage, converting a Florida room, or dealing with a bedroom that never gets cool? Ductless mini-splits are often the right answer — no ductwork, high efficiency (22+ SEER2), independent zoning, and quiet operation. We install and service Mitsubishi, LG, and Fujitsu ductless systems.</p>

  <h2>Financing that makes sense</h2>
  <p>Replacing a system is a big decision. We partner with Synchrony to offer <a href="/financing/">HVAC financing options</a> including 0% promotional rates, 10+ year fixed terms, and instant soft-credit pre-approval. Many customers find their monthly payment is less than the monthly savings on their electric bill from a high-efficiency system.</p>

